Harry Tyson-Wilson (born 29 December 1996) is an English professional rugby league footballer who plays for Sheffield Eagles in the Betfred Championship. He plays as a scrum-half.
He has played for Hull FC, Doncaster (loan), York City Knights (two spells, one as a loan), and for Hunslet in League 1, as a scrum-half.
Harry is the brother of prop Bobby Tyson-Wilson, who also plays for Sheffield Eagles.
